2. Circular cylinder mounted on the flat bed of an open channel for Reynolds numbers defined with the cylinder diameter, D, smaller than 4460.
3. The structure of the HV system in the periodic breakaway sub-regime, which is ~={purple}characterized by the formation of three main necklace vortices=~. Over one oscillation cycle of the previously observed ~={purple}breakaway sub-regime=~	
